I don't think even with a lot of training.

01:43:03.350 --> 01:43:08.300
But let's say that you want
to improve your performance

01:43:08.300 --> 01:43:09.770
in a given type of exercise.

01:43:09.770 --> 01:43:12.370
Let's talk about some of
the things that seem to work

01:43:12.370 --> 01:43:17.050
across the board to improve
strength, improve hypertrophy,

01:43:17.050 --> 01:43:20.720
and improve nerve to muscle
communication and performance.

01:43:20.720 --> 01:43:22.640
The first thing that's absolutely key

01:43:22.640 --> 01:43:25.890
for nerve to muscle communication
and physical performance

01:43:25.890 --> 01:43:28.630
of any kind might not
sound that exciting to you

01:43:28.630 --> 01:43:30.750
but it is very exciting.

01:43:30.750 --> 01:43:32.033
And that's salt.

01:43:33.307 --> 01:43:36.560
Nerves cells, neurons
communicate with each other

01:43:36.560 --> 01:43:39.840
and communicate with
muscle by electricity.

01:43:39.840 --> 01:43:43.530
But that electricity is generated
by particular ions moving

01:43:43.530 --> 01:43:45.160
into and out of the neuron.

01:43:45.160 --> 01:43:50.160
And the rushing in of a
particular ion, sodium, salt

01:43:50.380 --> 01:43:52.890
is what allows nerve cells to fire.

01:43:52.890 --> 01:43:55.880
If you don't have enough
salt in your system

01:43:55.880 --> 01:43:57.740
your neurons and your brain and your nerve

01:43:57.740 --> 01:44:00.620
to muscle communication will be terrible.

01:44:00.620 --> 01:44:03.720
If you have sufficient
salt, it will be excellent.

01:44:03.720 --> 01:44:06.320
How much salt will depend on
how much water you're drinking,

01:44:06.320 --> 01:44:07.610
how much caffeine you're drinking,

01:44:07.610 --> 01:44:09.390
and how much food you're ingesting.

01:44:09.390 --> 01:44:11.960
And whether or not you're
taking any diuretics

01:44:11.960 --> 01:44:14.270
how hot it is, et cetera,
how much you're sweating.

01:44:14.270 --> 01:44:16.040
So you want to make sure
that you have enough salt,

01:44:16.040 --> 01:44:18.160
potassium and magnesium in your system

01:44:18.160 --> 01:44:19.700
if you want to perform well.

01:44:19.700 --> 01:44:23.370
I realized that salt isn't
very glamorous performance tool

01:44:23.370 --> 01:44:24.800
but it is a vital.

01:44:24.800 --> 01:44:26.040
Its absolutely vital.

01:44:26.040 --> 01:44:28.010
And the endurance athletes
and the people that train

01:44:28.010 --> 01:44:30.950
in high heat can speak to the fact that

01:44:30.950 --> 01:44:34.360
when your electrolytes are low,
your brain doesn't function,

01:44:34.360 --> 01:44:36.070
your body doesn't function nearly as well.

01:44:36.070 --> 01:44:39.210
In fact, even for mental
work, for studying

01:44:39.210 --> 01:44:42.530
and for writing and for
doing math and coding,

01:44:42.530 --> 01:44:43.870
doing analytic work of any kind,

01:44:43.870 --> 01:44:46.870
even a hard conversation
that's important to you,

01:44:46.870 --> 01:44:48.870
having sufficient electrolytes
is really going to help

01:44:48.870 --> 01:44:51.040
and being low on electrolytes won't help

01:44:51.040 --> 01:44:52.360
and just drinking water won't help

01:44:52.360 --> 01:44:54.640
because you need electrolytes.

01:44:54.640 --> 01:44:57.860
The other thing that's been
shown over and over again,

01:44:57.860 --> 01:44:59.940
a numerous well-controlled studies

01:44:59.940 --> 01:45:03.370
to improve muscle performance is creatine.

01:45:03.370 --> 01:45:06.150
Early on there was a lot of
controversy about creatine

01:45:06.150 --> 01:45:08.610
but there are many studies
if you want, you can go

01:45:08.610 --> 01:45:10.900
to this website that
everyone now knows I love

01:45:10.900 --> 01:45:13.900
which is this free website examined.com

01:45:13.900 --> 01:45:17.300
that there are no fewer
than 18 studies there.

01:45:17.300 --> 01:45:19.350
66 studies...

01:45:19.350 --> 01:45:22.280
So 18 studies supporting
that muscle creating content

01:45:22.280 --> 01:45:24.300
can be increased by ingesting creatine.

01:45:24.300 --> 01:45:25.250
How much creatine?

01:45:25.250 --> 01:45:28.440
Well, I asked the experts and they tell me

01:45:28.440 --> 01:45:31.810
that for somebody who is about 180 pounds,

01:45:31.810 --> 01:45:35.160
five grams a day should
be sufficient or so.

01:45:35.160 --> 01:45:36.870
Heavier than 180, so if you got like

01:45:36.870 --> 01:45:39.740
if you're a 220 pound or 230 pound person,

01:45:39.740 --> 01:45:41.610
10 to 15 grams of creatine.

01:45:41.610 --> 01:45:43.110
People lighter than 180 pounds

01:45:43.110 --> 01:45:45.900
maybe three to five grams of creatine

01:45:45.900 --> 01:45:47.350
or even one to three grams.

01:45:47.350 --> 01:45:52.350
Creatine is a fuel source for
early in bouts of activity

01:45:53.340 --> 01:45:54.800
for high intensity activity.

01:45:54.800 --> 01:45:57.970
It is also a fuel source
for neurons in the brain

01:45:57.970 --> 01:46:01.620
and it can have some
cognitive enhancing effects.

01:46:01.620 --> 01:46:03.350
So creatine is a very
interesting molecule.

01:46:03.350 --> 01:46:06.103
Early on when it was
released as a supplement,

01:46:07.644 --> 01:46:09.620
it was thought that you had to load it

01:46:09.620 --> 01:46:11.160
in higher dosages for a few days

01:46:11.160 --> 01:46:14.210
and then maintain it at lower dosages.

01:46:14.210 --> 01:46:16.040
So you'd take 20 or 30 grams a day

01:46:16.040 --> 01:46:17.900
then back off to five or 10.

01:46:17.900 --> 01:46:19.030
It doesn't seem to be the case

01:46:19.030 --> 01:46:20.010
that you can get all the benefits

01:46:20.010 --> 01:46:22.970
from taking the dosages at the low level.

01:46:22.970 --> 01:46:24.960
I just mentioned a few moments ago

01:46:24.960 --> 01:46:27.010
as they relate to body weight throughout.

01:46:27.010 --> 01:46:30.290
So salt and electrolytes absolutely key.

01:46:30.290 --> 01:46:31.123
You need those present.

01:46:31.123 --> 01:46:32.490
You need to be well hydrated.

01:46:33.460 --> 01:46:36.560
Creatine seems to have a
performance enhancing effect.

01:46:36.560 --> 01:46:41.550
There are 66 studies, 66
showing that power output

01:46:41.550 --> 01:46:46.200
is greatly increased
anywhere from 1%2 to 20%.

01:46:46.200 --> 01:46:47.600
And this is sprinting and running

01:46:47.600 --> 01:46:50.670
and jumping as well as
weightlifting by creatine.

01:46:50.670 --> 01:46:54.530
The ability to hydrate
your body is improved

01:46:54.530 --> 01:46:58.120
by creating because of the
way that it brings more water

